Exponential health utility. A characterization and comments on the contribution 
by Happich and Muhlbacher.

Osterdal LP(1).

Author information:
(1)Institute of Economics, University of Copenhagen, Denmark. 
lars.p.osterdal@econ.ku.dk

Comment on
    Eur J Health Econ. 2003 Nov;4(4):292-4.

In a recent contribution Happich and Muhlbacher proposed an axiom of constant 
absolute trade-off of life-years for health states, and studied the family of 
QALY models satisfying this axiom under expected utility and mutual utility 
independence between life-years and health states. Here we provide a complete 
characterization of the family of QALY models satisfying these conditions. This 
family should not be mistaken for the family of multiplicative exponential QALY 
models; in particular, it violates the zero condition.

