As life expectancy and modern surgical and intensive care techniques develop, 
the number of old patients in surgery is rising. Associated are problems with 
the indication for surgical intervention and rising incidence of "typical" peri- 
and postoperative complications such as postoperative delirium. Geriatric 
assessment serves to identify patients at risk of developing complications, to 
