Osteo-articular complications of sickle cell anaemia in adult are represented by 
bone marrow infarcts, osteomyelitis and osteonecrosis of femoral and humeral 
heads. The frequency and/or the severity of these complications provide a great 
functional disability in young patients whose life expectancy is growing. A well 
adapted treatment would may limit the sequels.

